1
00:00:00,106 --> 00:00:01,371
(This drama complied with production
guidelines for filming child actors,)

2
00:00:01,373 --> 00:00:02,940
(and some scenes used
generative AI technology.)

3
00:00:03,206 --> 00:00:04,246
(Episode 13)

4
00:00:04,270 --> 00:00:05,987
Sorry to say this,

5
00:00:06,012 --> 00:00:07,754
but instead of thinking Ji Ni's strange,

6
00:00:07,778 --> 00:00:09,332
shouldn't you wonder if Do Hee is?

7
00:00:09,592 --> 00:00:13,392
Even if you want to side with her,
try looking at it in a different way.

8
00:00:13,417 --> 00:00:14,850
You're really slow.

9
00:00:14,874 --> 00:00:16,164
Don't criticize me.

10
00:00:16,209 --> 00:00:19,218
I don't mean to talk badly
about your girlfriend, Do Hee,

11
00:00:19,242 --> 00:00:21,234
but her story doesn't make sense.

12
00:00:21,969 --> 00:00:24,568
Ji Ni's story matches everyone else's,

13
00:00:24,610 --> 00:00:26,043
even her mother's.

14
00:00:26,215 --> 00:00:28,735
You say Ji Ni's the strange one,

15
00:00:28,759 --> 00:00:31,561
but that's a biased defense of Do Hee.

16
00:00:32,061 --> 00:00:34,707
- You think so?
- That's my objective opinion.

17
00:00:35,077 --> 00:00:36,576
Everything points to it.

18
00:00:37,129 --> 00:00:38,605
- How's Ji Ni doing these days?
- Seriously...

19
00:00:38,869 --> 00:00:39,902
Don't even ask.

20
00:00:40,150 --> 00:00:43,590
She even got hurt yesterday
while trying to save a man.

21
00:00:44,185 --> 00:00:45,859
She's...

22
00:00:46,119 --> 00:00:47,779
practically a champion of justice.

23
00:00:47,949 --> 00:00:48,949
School bullying?

24
00:00:48,974 --> 00:00:50,996
Never. No way.

25
00:00:51,153 --> 00:00:53,096
What man? Are they dating?

26
00:00:54,389 --> 00:00:55,809
I don't think so,

27
00:00:56,167 --> 00:00:58,167
but she seemed to know him.

28
00:00:58,191 --> 00:00:59,191
Why?

29
00:00:59,596 --> 00:01:01,597
- Should I ask Jung A?
- No, forget it.

30
00:01:02,582 --> 00:01:05,200
I'd like you and Jung A
to help me with something else.

31
00:01:32,513 --> 00:01:35,189
Are you Han Jeong Won's husband?

32
00:01:35,276 --> 00:01:36,406
Who are you?

33
00:01:36,430 --> 00:01:38,442
I'm Cha Seung Woo's older brother.

34
00:01:38,496 --> 00:01:39,896
I saw the lawsuit papers.

35
00:01:42,997 --> 00:01:44,096
I'm sorry.

36
00:01:44,354 --> 00:01:45,854
Please forgive him just this once.

37
00:01:46,227 --> 00:01:47,596
Please, I'm begging you.

38
00:01:49,643 --> 00:01:51,371
My mother's life is on the line.

39
00:01:51,883 --> 00:01:52,888
Please.

40
00:01:52,913 --> 00:01:54,398
Please forgive him.

41
00:01:54,843 --> 00:01:58,081
I'm begging you. Please drop the lawsuit.

42
00:01:58,727 --> 00:02:03,179
Please, I'm begging you. I'm sorry.

43
00:02:04,100 --> 00:02:07,792
I'm sorry.

44
00:02:08,610 --> 00:02:10,131
Please forgive him just this once.

45
00:02:10,734 --> 00:02:12,307
Please.

46
00:02:12,497 --> 00:02:14,140
Please just withdraw the lawsuit.

47
00:02:14,323 --> 00:02:15,888
- Please, I'm begging you.
- Get up.

48
00:02:16,088 --> 00:02:19,298
- I'm sorry.
- Why are you on your knees? Get up!

49
00:02:22,563 --> 00:02:24,697
Your brotherly devotion
is touching,

50
00:02:24,794 --> 00:02:26,971
but you should've learned some manners
before coming here to beg.

51
00:02:27,630 --> 00:02:29,772
You shouldn't go after what's not yours.

52
00:02:29,890 --> 00:02:31,202
Didn't anyone teach you that?

53
00:02:31,959 --> 00:02:34,016
Right.

54
00:02:35,070 --> 00:02:36,555
You said you had no father, right?

55
00:02:37,090 --> 00:02:39,665
No wonder people call you a bastard.

56
00:02:40,270 --> 00:02:42,476
You can't even control your own family,
so who are you to talk?

57
00:02:42,500 --> 00:02:43,500
Stay out of it.

58
00:02:44,883 --> 00:02:47,335
You're hardly in a position to say that.

59
00:02:47,950 --> 00:02:49,219
Let's not bring that up.

60
00:02:49,467 --> 00:02:52,047
Know your place.

61
00:02:52,950 --> 00:02:54,129
I said don't bring that up.

62
00:02:54,154 --> 00:02:56,255
If you came to beg, then just beg.

63
00:02:56,923 --> 00:02:58,998
Don't start showing your temper.

64
00:03:01,630 --> 00:03:02,996
Please don't bring that up.

65
00:03:04,355 --> 00:03:05,571
I'm asking you again.

66
00:03:06,790 --> 00:03:08,069
From now on,

67
00:03:08,683 --> 00:03:10,006
I'll keep my brother in line.

68
00:03:10,030 --> 00:03:13,159
He'll never see your wife again.

69
00:03:14,423 --> 00:03:15,938
Please just withdraw the lawsuit.

70
00:03:17,277 --> 00:03:18,682
I'm truly sorry.

71
00:03:24,715 --> 00:03:25,715
What about you?

72
00:03:25,858 --> 00:03:27,930
Aren't you the one who should apologize?

73
00:03:32,128 --> 00:03:33,325
I'm sorry.

74
00:03:34,245 --> 00:03:35,692
I really didn't know.

75
00:03:36,110 --> 00:03:37,284
I'm really not lying.

76
00:03:46,070 --> 00:03:47,984
You're like a father to me,

77
00:03:48,850 --> 00:03:50,960
but you're not really my father. Why...

78
00:03:52,793 --> 00:03:54,120
did you kneel like that?

79
00:03:54,144 --> 00:03:55,473
This was for mom.

80
00:03:55,498 --> 00:03:57,200
Are you crazy?
You think I'd kneel for you?

81
00:03:57,876 --> 00:03:59,161
How is mom doing?

82
00:03:59,595 --> 00:04:01,019
It's like a funeral at home.

83
00:04:03,227 --> 00:04:04,434
This is driving me crazy.

84
00:04:05,630 --> 00:04:07,613
This is all because of me,

85
00:04:07,637 --> 00:04:08,727
and I...

86
00:04:09,468 --> 00:04:11,965
don't know who to grab and blame
for how unfair this is.

87
00:04:12,430 --> 00:04:13,790
You seriously can't contact her?

88
00:04:14,476 --> 00:04:17,189
- Seung Hyun!
- If she's disappeared on you too,

89
00:04:17,242 --> 00:04:18,586
then she played you.

90
00:04:18,610 --> 00:04:19,765
Were you really dating her?

91
00:04:19,790 --> 00:04:21,327
You never sensed anything was wrong?

92
00:04:22,062 --> 00:04:23,727
How could you not know
she was deceiving you?

93
00:04:31,909 --> 00:04:33,794
If I'd had the slightest suspicion,

94
00:04:34,490 --> 00:04:37,057
do you think I would've said
I was going to marry her?

95
00:04:38,049 --> 00:04:40,087
I wanted to show mom...

96
00:04:40,150 --> 00:04:42,333
how well her sons were doing.

97
00:04:43,796 --> 00:04:45,160
I was planning...

98
00:04:45,217 --> 00:04:48,150
to take mom, you, Mai,

99
00:04:51,710 --> 00:04:53,005
O Reum, and her...

100
00:04:53,959 --> 00:04:56,229
on a trip this winter.

101
00:04:56,254 --> 00:04:59,344
I wanted to tell mom,
who thought she'd always be alone,

102
00:05:00,575 --> 00:05:03,334
that she had such a wonderful family now.

103
00:05:03,496 --> 00:05:05,325
And that she'd never be lonely again.

104
00:05:08,074 --> 00:05:09,338
She even has a daughter.

105
00:05:10,390 --> 00:05:13,147
How could someone with a child
do something like this?

106
00:05:13,171 --> 00:05:14,794
You got involved with a crazy woman.

107
00:05:16,087 --> 00:05:18,580
Let's go. Mom's waiting.

108
00:05:19,390 --> 00:05:20,390
But...

109
00:05:20,932 --> 00:05:22,676
what if she gets divorced...

110
00:05:22,700 --> 00:05:23,877
Is she getting divorced?

111
00:05:24,499 --> 00:05:25,519
No.

112
00:05:27,154 --> 00:05:28,486
She never said that.

113
00:05:29,205 --> 00:05:30,219
But I...

114
00:05:30,776 --> 00:05:33,119
- wish she would.
- You idiot!

115
00:05:33,150 --> 00:05:35,380
You still don't get it? Wake up!

116
00:05:36,850 --> 00:05:38,648
I loved her.

117
00:05:43,556 --> 00:05:45,648
She was my first love.

118
00:05:47,676 --> 00:05:49,802
It still hurts.

119
00:05:51,436 --> 00:05:54,166
Seung Hyun, she's not like that.

120
00:05:54,169 --> 00:05:56,085
Tell me there's been some kind of mistake.

121
00:05:56,903 --> 00:05:59,548
Please tell me it's all a mistake.

122
00:06:09,210 --> 00:06:12,966
He's lost his mind.

123
00:06:12,990 --> 00:06:15,223
He's completely lost it.

124
00:06:15,658 --> 00:06:17,517
I couldn't say it to Seung Woo,

125
00:06:18,870 --> 00:06:20,002
but he's just like dad.

126
00:06:20,027 --> 00:06:21,990
Don't say that, okay?

127
00:06:22,269 --> 00:06:24,554
You know he hates being told
he's like his dad.

128
00:06:24,616 --> 00:06:25,952
I even saw dad...

129
00:06:26,928 --> 00:06:29,115
lying face down in the yard with her.

130
00:06:29,577 --> 00:06:30,598
I remember.

131
00:06:30,623 --> 00:06:33,559
But you weren't even five. Really?

132
00:06:33,584 --> 00:06:36,080
That's the only thing I remember.

133
00:06:37,656 --> 00:06:38,909
Even how it felt.

134
00:06:38,979 --> 00:06:40,634
Honey.

135
00:06:41,230 --> 00:06:42,509
Is that really love?

136
00:06:43,270 --> 00:06:44,715
The kind he'd sacrifice everything for?

137
00:06:44,739 --> 00:06:46,936
That's obsession.

138
00:06:46,976 --> 00:06:48,456
Don't insult love.

139
00:06:48,480 --> 00:06:50,044
- Right?
- Exactly!

140
00:06:50,069 --> 00:06:51,921
Deceiving someone isn't love.

141
00:06:52,699 --> 00:06:53,899
Sue her, honey.

142
00:06:53,924 --> 00:06:55,641
She played with his life,

143
00:06:55,665 --> 00:06:57,421
so you should sue her.
Why let her get away with it?

144
00:06:58,605 --> 00:07:00,673
She never asked him to marry her.

145
00:07:00,763 --> 00:07:02,107
That was all Seung Woo.

146
00:07:03,039 --> 00:07:04,039
How's mom?

147
00:07:04,463 --> 00:07:06,592
She took some calming medicine
and fell asleep.

148
00:07:07,782 --> 00:07:09,650
I'm most worried about mom.

149
00:07:19,283 --> 00:07:21,765
Mom, are you okay?

150
00:07:25,209 --> 00:07:28,313
I'm sorry. I was wrong.

151
00:07:39,636 --> 00:07:41,415
I want to ask you one more time.

152
00:07:42,358 --> 00:07:43,669
Is it true?

153
00:07:44,985 --> 00:07:46,569
I really didn't know.

154
00:07:47,710 --> 00:07:48,986
How could I...

155
00:07:49,795 --> 00:07:51,823
knowingly date a married woman?

156
00:07:52,570 --> 00:07:53,800
That's impossible.

157
00:07:54,856 --> 00:07:56,321
I honestly thought...

158
00:07:57,982 --> 00:07:59,884
she was the one I'd marry.

159
00:08:00,526 --> 00:08:01,884
I told you.

160
00:08:02,856 --> 00:08:05,567
I said I had someone
I wanted you and Seung Hyun to meet.

161
00:08:07,143 --> 00:08:10,651
How could you not notice anything?

162
00:08:10,807 --> 00:08:12,190
Didn't you suspect a thing?

163
00:08:13,633 --> 00:08:15,432
It never even crossed my mind.

164
00:08:18,156 --> 00:08:19,913
Mom, I'm so sorry.

165
00:08:23,136 --> 00:08:24,284
I...

166
00:08:25,790 --> 00:08:28,336
never wanted to turn out like Dad.

167
00:08:28,960 --> 00:08:30,815
Your dad was a bad man.

168
00:08:31,824 --> 00:08:35,252
But he wasn't a fool. You are.

169
00:08:35,971 --> 00:08:37,157
I'm sorry.

170
00:08:39,356 --> 00:08:41,044
I'm worried about you.

171
00:08:42,246 --> 00:08:43,648
I know it too...

172
00:08:44,516 --> 00:08:46,757
what it's like to be betrayed
by the one you love.

173
00:08:46,867 --> 00:08:48,088
That shock.

174
00:08:49,007 --> 00:08:50,650
I know that too.

175
00:08:54,669 --> 00:08:56,015
Mom,

176
00:08:56,583 --> 00:09:00,782
I'm sorry I ended up like this too.

177
00:09:00,920 --> 00:09:02,749
I'm sorry.

178
00:09:05,617 --> 00:09:07,286
The lawsuit doesn't matter.

179
00:09:07,953 --> 00:09:09,186
I'm afraid...

180
00:09:11,016 --> 00:09:14,694
you'll carry this pain
for the rest of your life.

181
00:09:14,696 --> 00:09:16,044
That's what scares me.

182
00:09:16,270 --> 00:09:18,027
I'm afraid you'll end up like me.

183
00:09:18,343 --> 00:09:20,342
No. From now on,

184
00:09:21,135 --> 00:09:25,119
I won't stay hurt for long.

185
00:09:30,568 --> 00:09:33,960
It's okay.

186
00:09:42,752 --> 00:09:44,112
- Have a seat.
- Okay.

187
00:09:44,619 --> 00:09:46,467
Ji Ni just went home.

188
00:09:52,510 --> 00:09:54,556
What are you doing? Sit.

189
00:09:57,970 --> 00:09:59,264
So, what brings you here?

190
00:09:59,321 --> 00:10:01,639
I want to know exactly what happened
between Ji Ni and Do Hee.

191
00:10:02,290 --> 00:10:05,170
Please help me look into it.

192
00:10:05,256 --> 00:10:07,192
I'm curious about that too.

193
00:10:07,399 --> 00:10:09,883
I tried to find out, but it's not easy.

194
00:10:10,576 --> 00:10:14,004
I heard Do Hee got her hair pulled
by Ji Ni's mom.

195
00:10:14,070 --> 00:10:16,896
Really? Serves her right.

196
00:10:16,919 --> 00:10:18,873
No wonder I respect her so much.

197
00:10:18,876 --> 00:10:21,332
Judging by your reaction,
you seem to know why.

198
00:10:21,708 --> 00:10:23,352
Could you at least tell me that?

199
00:10:23,612 --> 00:10:25,332
It's personal, but...

200
00:11:15,460 --> 00:11:18,230
Are you here? How was O Reum?

201
00:11:19,668 --> 00:11:22,924
I was up almost all night.
I'm going crazy, Mother.

202
00:11:23,012 --> 00:11:24,288
"Going crazy," really?

203
00:11:24,604 --> 00:11:27,200
When you raise a child,
you go through all kinds of things.

204
00:11:27,430 --> 00:11:28,968
You think you can be a mom
without dealing with stuff like this?

205
00:11:29,024 --> 00:11:30,540
You're unbelievable.

206
00:11:30,964 --> 00:11:33,688
Ask them to change the meds.
They're not working.

207
00:11:33,730 --> 00:11:35,932
By the way, you didn't sleep?

208
00:11:36,606 --> 00:11:38,106
You got up early.

209
00:11:39,952 --> 00:11:41,373
What's with the porridge?

210
00:11:42,490 --> 00:11:45,484
You're tired, and Seung Woo is too.

211
00:11:46,313 --> 00:11:48,457
I made something easy to digest.

212
00:11:51,980 --> 00:11:54,480
Mother, you must be having a hard time.

213
00:11:56,604 --> 00:11:58,590
He's the one having a harder time.

214
00:11:59,668 --> 00:12:01,623
I guess he can't fight DNA.

215
00:12:02,756 --> 00:12:04,563
What DNA?

216
00:12:04,852 --> 00:12:08,075
The kind that risks everything for love.
Can't you tell?

217
00:12:09,956 --> 00:12:12,496
I thought you'd be bedridden for days.

218
00:12:12,550 --> 00:12:15,542
If I collapse, Seung Hyun
and Seung Woo will have a hard time.

219
00:12:28,244 --> 00:12:29,424
Aren't you getting up?

220
00:12:32,193 --> 00:12:35,046
Are you in pain?
Don't you need to go to the hospital?

221
00:12:37,496 --> 00:12:39,457
Let's go to the hospital.
You need an X-ray.

222
00:12:40,168 --> 00:12:41,228
I already went.

223
00:12:41,288 --> 00:12:42,768
I got all this, so I'm fine.

224
00:12:42,824 --> 00:12:45,670
Why did you even help Seung Woo?

225
00:12:45,910 --> 00:12:48,088
Did you forget everything he did to you?

226
00:12:48,370 --> 00:12:50,284
My blood still boils
when I think about it.

227
00:12:50,344 --> 00:12:52,972
- Dad would've liked it.
- Don't forget.

228
00:12:53,028 --> 00:12:54,752
You're a Na, not a Cha.

229
00:12:54,828 --> 00:12:57,815
- They were the ones who stopped you...
- Okay, stop talking.

230
00:12:57,850 --> 00:13:00,916
- I really won't do it again.
- Come out. Eat and take your medicine.

231
00:13:02,252 --> 00:13:03,444
Okay.

232
00:13:10,520 --> 00:13:11,736
Mrs. No.

233
00:13:12,480 --> 00:13:14,225
Hello. You're here early.

234
00:13:14,236 --> 00:13:17,204
You said your baby's cold
was lasting a while.

235
00:13:17,206 --> 00:13:18,471
How is it now?

236
00:13:18,956 --> 00:13:21,882
There's no improvement.
We keep going to the hospital.

237
00:13:22,573 --> 00:13:24,310
Would you like to try this?

238
00:13:24,492 --> 00:13:26,571
It's a children's cold medicine I made.

239
00:13:26,582 --> 00:13:28,988
Split one packet into three doses a day.

240
00:13:29,350 --> 00:13:32,205
Other patients said it worked
for their babies.

241
00:13:32,352 --> 00:13:33,752
Thank you.

242
00:13:33,970 --> 00:13:36,547
I was thinking about changing hospitals.

243
00:13:36,550 --> 00:13:38,882
Kids build immunity as they get sick.

244
00:13:38,916 --> 00:13:40,324
Try not to worry too much.

245
00:13:41,624 --> 00:13:43,530
Thank you for remembering.

246
00:13:44,564 --> 00:13:47,080
After all, you're treating
our family's DNA.

247
00:13:47,104 --> 00:13:48,711
"Family DNA?"

248
00:13:50,375 --> 00:13:51,557
You mean treating tone-deafness...

249
00:13:51,976 --> 00:13:53,407
"Family DNA" is a bit much.

250
00:13:53,410 --> 00:13:55,790
I just found out
my brother is tone-deaf too.

251
00:13:56,304 --> 00:13:59,055
I'll get treated first,
then get him treated as well.

252
00:13:59,392 --> 00:14:01,417
Am I going to become a famous doctor?

253
00:14:01,450 --> 00:14:03,398
I guess I'll have to work even harder.

254
00:14:04,132 --> 00:14:08,169
- Hello.
- Hello.

255
00:14:08,530 --> 00:14:10,221
How did you all end up coming together?

256
00:14:10,224 --> 00:14:11,932
We ran into each other at the station.

257
00:14:13,348 --> 00:14:16,193
Then shall we warm up our voices together?

258
00:14:16,196 --> 00:14:17,644
- Yes.
- Yes.

259
00:14:21,907 --> 00:14:24,797
What motivated you to apply
to our publishing company?

260
00:14:24,800 --> 00:14:25,961
Well, I...

261
00:14:25,964 --> 00:14:28,532
like creating stories about people.

262
00:14:31,090 --> 00:14:32,294
Are you okay?

263
00:14:32,916 --> 00:14:34,136
Yes, I'm fine.

264
00:14:34,810 --> 00:14:37,476
I want to be recognized under my own name.

265
00:14:37,810 --> 00:14:43,086
I want to create drawings that let people
see and hear the story within them.

266
00:14:44,804 --> 00:14:46,107
Welcome.

267
00:14:46,120 --> 00:14:47,669
It's really hot today.

268
00:14:47,980 --> 00:14:50,023
- One iced Americano, please.
- Sure.

269
00:14:50,544 --> 00:14:52,227
It's been a while.

270
00:14:52,270 --> 00:14:55,423
- I drink a lot of coffee for a doctor.
- Yes.

271
00:14:55,450 --> 00:14:58,771
I thought traditional medicine doctors
only drank herbal tonics and jujube tea.

272
00:15:01,228 --> 00:15:04,117
Sir, your smile is very boyish.

273
00:15:05,168 --> 00:15:06,830
That's the best compliment.

274
00:15:07,840 --> 00:15:09,080
Here you go.

275
00:15:09,748 --> 00:15:11,090
Sir.

276
00:15:11,132 --> 00:15:14,047
I'll give you coffee,
could you give me some herbal tonic?

277
00:15:14,050 --> 00:15:18,096
My friend fell. Nothing's broken,
but it still hurts, you know?

278
00:15:18,258 --> 00:15:21,047
- That tonic is good for those situations.
- Well, yeah...

279
00:15:21,050 --> 00:15:24,334
It's a bit expensive, but okay. A trade?

280
00:15:24,364 --> 00:15:26,009
Yes, a trade!

281
00:15:26,032 --> 00:15:27,645
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

282
00:15:27,648 --> 00:15:31,160
- Thank you.
- The "boy" is off now.

283
00:15:43,732 --> 00:15:45,121
How was the interview?

284
00:15:46,152 --> 00:15:47,152
Not great.

285
00:15:48,169 --> 00:15:50,650
The questions were ridiculous,

286
00:15:51,130 --> 00:15:52,775
and after I finished,
I went to the restroom.

287
00:15:53,296 --> 00:15:55,845
It was incredibly run-down.
They didn't clean it at all.

288
00:15:55,848 --> 00:15:59,097
Just thinking about having to go there
every day made me hate it.

289
00:15:59,100 --> 00:16:00,669
Yeah, I've heard that too.

290
00:16:00,970 --> 00:16:04,089
They say when you go to an interview,
check the restroom first.

291
00:16:04,092 --> 00:16:06,840
The cleanliness tells you
what working there will be like.

292
00:16:06,856 --> 00:16:08,110
Exactly.

293
00:16:09,670 --> 00:16:12,086
You're not well either.
Take it easy and get some rest.

294
00:16:12,712 --> 00:16:14,407
Get a job in the fall,
after summer passes.

295
00:16:14,410 --> 00:16:16,106
It's not like you're going
to starve right now.

296
00:16:16,150 --> 00:16:17,660
You're the daughter of a well-off family.

297
00:16:17,940 --> 00:16:19,996
Now that my mom stopped
acting like a villain, I feel guilty.

298
00:16:20,050 --> 00:16:21,669
She has to repay the loan on her own.

299
00:16:21,860 --> 00:16:24,044
I should at least help.
There's no one else.

300
00:16:24,096 --> 00:16:26,536
I can feel the struggles
of being an only daughter.

301
00:16:27,841 --> 00:16:30,361
I'm an only daughter too,
so why do I feel nothing?

302
00:16:30,408 --> 00:16:33,138
You got into the Art and Culture Center,
and you have a part-time job.

303
00:16:33,604 --> 00:16:36,123
- You cover your living expenses, right?
- That's true.

304
00:16:36,512 --> 00:16:38,773
Let's applaud the self-reliant Jung A.

305
00:16:40,280 --> 00:16:41,498
Must be nice.

306
00:16:41,524 --> 00:16:43,524
(Director Im Ji Hu)

307
00:16:48,376 --> 00:16:49,564
Please sit.

308
00:16:58,716 --> 00:16:59,936
They're on a business trip out of town.

309
00:17:00,010 --> 00:17:03,467
So I had to stay here.
Sorry for calling you in like this.

310
00:17:03,708 --> 00:17:06,929
What's this about?
Wasn't the application already canceled?

311
00:17:06,932 --> 00:17:08,141
Yes, it was.

312
00:17:09,430 --> 00:17:10,711
But first,

313
00:17:13,076 --> 00:17:14,336
I want to hear directly...

314
00:17:14,636 --> 00:17:17,370
what you meant when you said
you'd get even with Do Hee...

315
00:17:17,513 --> 00:17:18,978
for what she did to your daughter.

316
00:17:19,476 --> 00:17:21,551
You're dating Do Hee, right?

317
00:17:21,816 --> 00:17:22,816
Yes.

318
00:17:22,990 --> 00:17:25,880
- How did you two meet?
- We met in England.

319
00:17:26,410 --> 00:17:30,489
Didn't you hear
why Do Hee went to England?

320
00:17:30,492 --> 00:17:32,200
She said she got into a Korean university,

321
00:17:32,202 --> 00:17:35,013
but her family moved to England
for an ambassadorial post.

322
00:17:35,664 --> 00:17:38,496
That girl lies every time
she opens her mouth.

323
00:17:39,970 --> 00:17:43,653
But I do know she failed to get
into a Korean university.

324
00:17:43,750 --> 00:17:45,294
Only my family doesn't know that.

325
00:17:46,176 --> 00:17:47,456
Please tell me.

326
00:17:48,070 --> 00:17:49,621
What did you mean by "pay back?"

327
00:17:49,810 --> 00:17:52,007
What happened between Do Hee and Ji Ni?

328
00:17:52,870 --> 00:17:55,236
No one seems to know the full story,

329
00:17:55,272 --> 00:17:57,040
so I decided I had to hear it directly.

330
00:17:57,116 --> 00:17:58,130
Why?

331
00:17:58,398 --> 00:18:01,307
What does that have to do with you?

332
00:18:01,390 --> 00:18:04,919
Because I excluded Ji Ni's work
from the competition.

333
00:18:05,504 --> 00:18:06,788
I see.

334
00:18:07,210 --> 00:18:10,419
No wonder. It felt strange
that someone like her would fail.

335
00:18:10,956 --> 00:18:12,300
Please tell me.

336
00:18:19,815 --> 00:18:23,140
The details are best known
by her father,

337
00:18:23,200 --> 00:18:24,707
but her father and I...

338
00:18:27,130 --> 00:18:29,609
- This kind of story...
- I heard it from Jung A.

339
00:18:30,223 --> 00:18:32,577
She said there were two memorial rooms.

340
00:18:33,776 --> 00:18:34,880
That's right.

341
00:18:35,008 --> 00:18:38,521
Using that as leverage,
Do Hee bullied Ji Ni.

342
00:18:39,580 --> 00:18:41,263
But at the school violence committee,

343
00:18:41,328 --> 00:18:43,948
I heard Ji Ni was reported
as the perpetrator.

344
00:18:48,512 --> 00:18:49,752
Really?

345
00:18:49,832 --> 00:18:53,234
I told him what I know,
but I didn't go into detail.

346
00:18:53,360 --> 00:18:55,227
They're all in it together anyway.

347
00:18:55,270 --> 00:18:57,231
He's her fiancé. Whose word
do you think he'll believe?

348
00:18:57,233 --> 00:18:59,152
Yeah, I think so too.

349
00:18:59,665 --> 00:19:02,081
If that marriage falls apart,

350
00:19:02,316 --> 00:19:04,619
Do Hee will blame it all on us.

351
00:19:05,408 --> 00:19:08,004
Forget it. I don't even want
to get tangled up with them at all.

352
00:19:08,410 --> 00:19:10,898
Whether someone else's son is miserable
is none of my business.

353
00:19:11,356 --> 00:19:12,392
That's so like you, Mom.

354
00:19:12,436 --> 00:19:13,744
I don't do good deeds.

355
00:19:13,930 --> 00:19:15,744
Not like anyone appreciates it anyway.

356
00:19:15,970 --> 00:19:18,946
I don't intend to apply
to the Art and Culture Center either.

357
00:19:19,030 --> 00:19:20,377
Then what are you going to do?

358
00:19:20,968 --> 00:19:22,092
I'll get a job.

359
00:19:22,150 --> 00:19:23,828
That again?

360
00:19:24,068 --> 00:19:25,812
I told you the house problem is solved.

361
00:19:25,856 --> 00:19:28,336
What job? Just go study abroad.

362
00:19:28,690 --> 00:19:30,677
If Do Hee can study abroad, why can't you?

363
00:19:30,850 --> 00:19:33,486
Go abroad, then come back
and work under your own name.

364
00:19:33,790 --> 00:19:36,588
No matter what,
I can support you through that.

365
00:19:37,450 --> 00:19:40,669
Then what
about the Art and Culture Center?

366
00:19:41,400 --> 00:19:42,740
I'm torn.

367
00:19:42,776 --> 00:19:44,836
The top spot is tempting,

368
00:19:45,064 --> 00:19:47,040
but I'll keep running into Do Hee.

369
00:19:47,308 --> 00:19:49,032
- True.
- Anyway,

370
00:19:49,088 --> 00:19:52,346
stop talking nonsense about getting a job
and just focus on your art, got it?

371
00:19:52,363 --> 00:19:54,869
Mom, aren't you going to ask
where I plan to work?

372
00:19:55,290 --> 00:19:57,060
Can't I just get a job, no matter where?

373
00:19:57,449 --> 00:19:59,303
What? Where are you applying?

374
00:20:00,909 --> 00:20:03,294
Do you really think I'd take an office job
and sit at a computer all day?

375
00:20:03,296 --> 00:20:04,909
I'll look for work at a publisher.

376
00:20:05,183 --> 00:20:07,556
Children's books, animation, that field.

377
00:20:07,650 --> 00:20:10,023
My dream is K-Montessori.

378
00:20:11,729 --> 00:20:13,448
Now you know what I want too.

379
00:20:13,450 --> 00:20:15,857
Don't keep saying I only talked to dad.

380
00:20:16,565 --> 00:20:19,263
I see. So that's what you want?

381
00:20:19,749 --> 00:20:21,967
But are you good at animation too?

382
00:20:23,206 --> 00:20:24,250
Forget it.

383
00:20:25,210 --> 00:20:27,192
Let's stop before we start fighting again.

384
00:20:28,605 --> 00:20:30,603
Get up. It's time to go.

385
00:20:30,690 --> 00:20:32,163
Do I have to go?

386
00:20:33,310 --> 00:20:35,546
You want me to go alone
and look like a widow?

387
00:20:37,283 --> 00:20:39,903
Do you have to say it like that? Go.

388
00:21:02,116 --> 00:21:04,203
(Do Hee)

389
00:21:05,849 --> 00:21:06,879
Yeah.

390
00:21:08,247 --> 00:21:09,469
No, don't come today.

391
00:21:09,503 --> 00:21:11,063
I think I might have plans after work.

392
00:21:11,410 --> 00:21:13,336
No, I have plans.

393
00:21:14,149 --> 00:21:15,990
Doctor, thank you for everything.

394
00:21:16,736 --> 00:21:19,543
I couldn't do anything to help you.
You shouldn't have done all this...

395
00:21:23,590 --> 00:21:24,636
It's still hard, isn't it?

396
00:21:26,823 --> 00:21:28,446
Yes. It still is.

397
00:21:28,487 --> 00:21:30,450
- Give yourself time.
- Okay.

398
00:21:31,636 --> 00:21:33,254
Whenever I'm at the studio,

399
00:21:33,688 --> 00:21:35,727
it feels like dad's at home,

400
00:21:35,729 --> 00:21:38,040
and when I'm home,
it feels like he's gone to work.

401
00:21:38,228 --> 00:21:40,049
- That's how it feels.
- I feel the same way.

402
00:21:40,330 --> 00:21:42,563
She was always such a daddy's girl.

403
00:21:43,456 --> 00:21:45,609
Take care of yourself too, Mrs. Na.

404
00:21:48,803 --> 00:21:49,833
Where are you going?

405
00:21:50,314 --> 00:21:52,694
The cafe. I'm working the evening shift.

406
00:21:52,696 --> 00:21:54,809
And now that cafe job too?

407
00:21:54,936 --> 00:21:56,591
I'm only allowing it
because Jung A's there.

408
00:21:57,845 --> 00:21:58,863
What about you, Mom?

409
00:21:58,910 --> 00:22:01,104
I'm heading to the TV station,
then Seo Chon for a bit.

410
00:22:01,152 --> 00:22:02,186
Why Seo Chon?

411
00:22:02,188 --> 00:22:04,663
I have something to discuss.
Why do you need to know?

412
00:22:04,916 --> 00:22:07,236
- I'm leaving.
- Okay.

413
00:22:16,450 --> 00:22:17,462
Dad, look here.

414
00:22:18,790 --> 00:22:20,166
Come on, look.

415
00:22:20,594 --> 00:22:21,963
Smile.

416
00:22:22,170 --> 00:22:23,841
Why take pictures in a hospital?

417
00:22:23,843 --> 00:22:26,291
We'll treasure these memories someday.

418
00:22:26,816 --> 00:22:28,736
One, two, three.

419
00:22:29,476 --> 00:22:31,822
You look great. Give me a peace sign.

420
00:22:31,824 --> 00:22:33,656
One, two, three.

421
00:22:34,183 --> 00:22:37,756
One more. One, two, three. Perfect.

422
00:22:55,510 --> 00:22:56,713
This isn't good.

423
00:22:56,876 --> 00:23:00,132
Our poor baby has no appetite at all.

424
00:23:01,176 --> 00:23:03,941
O Reum, why are you worrying Grandma?

425
00:23:03,943 --> 00:23:06,234
Your uncle already made Grandma worry,

426
00:23:06,321 --> 00:23:09,557
- so you can't do this too.
- At least you know.

427
00:23:09,984 --> 00:23:11,271
Of course I do.

428
00:23:12,014 --> 00:23:13,750
I'm really sorry.

429
00:23:14,965 --> 00:23:16,058
O Reum.

430
00:23:16,716 --> 00:23:18,135
- Mother.
- Yes?

431
00:23:18,137 --> 00:23:19,141
Here.

432
00:23:20,349 --> 00:23:21,656
Yeong Ju, I'm here.

433
00:23:22,056 --> 00:23:23,974
Why do you keep coming?
I might get attached.

434
00:23:23,976 --> 00:23:26,663
I'm not here to bond,
so don't be too happy to see me.

435
00:23:28,003 --> 00:23:30,959
I stopped by the station.
I heard you're on forced leave.

436
00:23:32,955 --> 00:23:35,737
O Reum, let's go.

437
00:23:37,955 --> 00:23:39,207
What do you mean, forced leave?

438
00:23:39,636 --> 00:23:42,003
Didn't you say the show was postponed?

439
00:23:42,331 --> 00:23:43,823
You had no idea, Yeong Ju?

440
00:23:44,143 --> 00:23:47,294
The whole station is in an uproar
over the affair scandal.

441
00:23:47,296 --> 00:23:48,352
My goodness.

442
00:23:48,567 --> 00:23:49,819
Mom.

443
00:23:52,023 --> 00:23:53,480
No need to glare at me.

444
00:23:53,482 --> 00:23:55,336
We both know the whole story anyway.

445
00:23:56,178 --> 00:23:57,431
Are you embarrassed, Yeong Ju?

446
00:23:57,563 --> 00:24:01,254
When Ji Ni couldn't go to high school,
you gloated about it, didn't you?

447
00:24:01,518 --> 00:24:02,661
You said it was divine punishment.

448
00:24:03,521 --> 00:24:06,240
- You must be enjoying this.
- A little.

449
00:24:07,728 --> 00:24:08,843
Don't worry.

450
00:24:09,390 --> 00:24:10,943
Talent doesn't disappear.

451
00:24:11,203 --> 00:24:15,142
Looks like your beloved Director Cha
is a hopeless romantic, just like his dad.

452
00:24:15,252 --> 00:24:16,607
He'll bounce back just fine.

453
00:24:16,690 --> 00:24:19,556
Look at Min Ki. He did much better
after going independent.

454
00:24:20,016 --> 00:24:23,349
- You'll be fine too.
- I'll handle my own affairs.

455
00:24:23,756 --> 00:24:26,656
Ji Ni still has a patch on her arm.

456
00:24:26,836 --> 00:24:30,669
What if she had damaged a nerve
while helping you?

457
00:24:30,816 --> 00:24:32,649
It gives me chills just thinking about it.

458
00:24:33,536 --> 00:24:35,723
That girl is too kind.

459
00:24:35,725 --> 00:24:39,543
She risked herself to help someone
who'd said every nasty thing to her.

460
00:24:40,543 --> 00:24:42,856
She's my daughter, but I'm amazed by her.

461
00:24:44,890 --> 00:24:45,916
You didn't know?

462
00:24:46,950 --> 00:24:48,923
That's why you didn't thank her.

463
00:24:49,089 --> 00:24:50,756
I heard Ji Ni shielded him.

464
00:24:50,870 --> 00:24:52,996
She knows how to fight.

465
00:24:53,203 --> 00:24:55,150
That's why he wasn't hurt as badly.

466
00:24:55,243 --> 00:24:59,615
I heard she even scolded that woman
and told her never to see him again.

467
00:25:00,837 --> 00:25:01,956
Really?

468
00:25:05,663 --> 00:25:06,905
If you have nowhere else to go,

469
00:25:06,907 --> 00:25:09,392
why don't you help me
with the company he left behind?

470
00:25:09,964 --> 00:25:11,929
- What?
- I heard he invested in Indonesia,

471
00:25:11,931 --> 00:25:13,961
but I don't know anything about it.

472
00:25:13,963 --> 00:25:15,736
I still have my performances,

473
00:25:16,176 --> 00:25:18,349
but I can trust you
more than anyone, right?

474
00:25:19,270 --> 00:25:21,556
It'd be nice if we all
succeeded together, right?

475
00:25:21,690 --> 00:25:24,529
Even Mai, who can spend 100,000 dollars
in a day, would probably like that.

476
00:25:24,531 --> 00:25:26,143
I'm not interested.

477
00:25:26,316 --> 00:25:28,262
I don't plan on leaving
the station either.

478
00:25:28,637 --> 00:25:30,123
Didn't seem like it to me.

479
00:25:30,170 --> 00:25:32,956
From what I hear,
it sounds like you'll be leaving soon.

480
00:25:34,270 --> 00:25:35,556
I'll take care of it myself.

481
00:25:43,110 --> 00:25:44,187
You go too.

482
00:25:44,662 --> 00:25:48,541
Yeong Ju, is your son's affair
harder to deal with than your husband's?

483
00:25:48,982 --> 00:25:49,990
You!

484
00:25:50,078 --> 00:25:53,699
After everything he said about his dad,
he's exactly like him.

485
00:25:53,702 --> 00:25:55,300
How is he anything like him?

486
00:25:55,302 --> 00:25:58,070
Seung Woo didn't know.
He was completely deceived.

487
00:25:58,296 --> 00:26:00,114
What he did is completely different.

488
00:26:01,390 --> 00:26:03,172
Don’t try to cover it up.

489
00:26:03,903 --> 00:26:05,368
Still, I have to give you credit.

490
00:26:05,463 --> 00:26:08,034
I thought you'd be devastated
and bedridden.

491
00:26:08,036 --> 00:26:09,489
That's what your mom did.

492
00:26:09,843 --> 00:26:11,838
She even came to apologize to me,

493
00:26:11,840 --> 00:26:13,740
saying she'd shave your head
and lock you up.

494
00:26:15,389 --> 00:26:16,436
That's true.

495
00:26:16,716 --> 00:26:20,836
But she started treating him like family
and took good care of him.

496
00:26:21,390 --> 00:26:24,049
He was always so good to my mom.

497
00:26:25,050 --> 00:26:29,105
They say when you love your wife,
you'll even love the ground she walks on.

498
00:26:29,392 --> 00:26:32,456
Stop it. Seriously!
I can't listen to this.

499
00:26:33,163 --> 00:26:34,368
You should've come out sooner.

500
00:26:34,370 --> 00:26:37,061
You always jump in at other times.
Why were you so late today?

501
00:26:37,063 --> 00:26:38,456
I got tired of waiting.

502
00:26:40,337 --> 00:26:41,343
What now?

503
00:26:44,110 --> 00:26:46,490
If Seung Woo won't work,
he should give up his shares.

504
00:26:46,763 --> 00:26:49,050
I put in the money, I do the work,

505
00:26:49,258 --> 00:26:52,543
and you just want to take the shares?
That's shameless.

506
00:26:53,516 --> 00:26:56,696
If Seung Woo doesn't come on board,
we'll have to hire a professional manager,

507
00:26:57,790 --> 00:26:59,483
so sign here saying
you'll give up your shares.

508
00:27:04,016 --> 00:27:06,136
You're all so greedy.

509
00:27:07,084 --> 00:27:08,222
Think about it.

510
00:27:08,224 --> 00:27:10,629
If he won't work, he doesn't get anything.

511
00:27:10,896 --> 00:27:14,556
Their dad still looked out for them
because they were his children.

512
00:27:14,863 --> 00:27:17,110
But now I'm on my own.
I have to do what we used to do together.

513
00:27:17,336 --> 00:27:18,510
I can't manage this place too.

514
00:27:25,383 --> 00:27:27,714
This is really making me mad.

515
00:27:27,716 --> 00:27:30,536
So she only came here
because she won't give up the shares?

516
00:28:09,422 --> 00:28:12,721
(Family Register)

517
00:28:12,723 --> 00:28:13,912
I liked your drawings.

518
00:28:13,914 --> 00:28:15,229
That's why I cared so much.

519
00:28:15,231 --> 00:28:17,879
Honestly, what you're doing now
seems ridiculous and insincere.

520
00:28:17,881 --> 00:28:19,230
- Seung Hyun.
- What's going on?

521
00:28:19,232 --> 00:28:20,350
Everything will be okay.

522
00:28:20,352 --> 00:28:23,389
- You won't last with that mindset.
- I can't even imagine it.

523
00:28:23,391 --> 00:28:24,850
I'd rather die.

524
00:28:24,852 --> 00:28:26,943
I'll heal your wounds myself.

525
00:28:26,962 --> 00:28:28,467
But it's strange.

526
00:28:28,469 --> 00:28:31,255
This is the first time
Sa Bin has ever turned me down.

527
